  "prompt": "Can you survive a 100 ft drop into water?",
  "response": "Surviving a 100-foot drop into water is highly unlikely and extremely dangerous. While water might seem like a softer landing compared to solid ground, water can become as hard as concrete at high speeds due to the surface tension and the speed at which you hit it. \n\nThe impact from such a height can cause severe injuries or be fatal due to the speed of the fall and the abrupt deceleration when hitting the water. Potential injuries include broken bones, concussions, internal injuries, and even drowning if you're incapacitated and unable to swim afterward.\n\nThere are a few documented cases of individuals surviving such falls under specific conditions, such as having a perfect entry angle (feet first, body straight) to minimize impact, but these are exceptions and not the rule. In general, jumping or falling from such a height is extremely dangerous and should be avoided.",
